{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Pin the release supply chain to immutable references\n\nMake every executable the release depends on identifiable by an immutable\nreference: full-SHA action pins, a hash-locked build environment, an\nexact-versioned + digest-verified MCP publisher, and non-persisted checkout\ncredentials. (Readiness Finding 4 — verified VALID against `release.yml`\nlines 31/32/43/60/65/85/124/129 and `pyproject.toml:1-3`.)\n\n## Why\n\nTwo release runs of the same rebar SHA can execute different build/upload/publish\ncode today. `release.yml` references first-party actions by moving major-version\ntags (`actions/checkout@v7` at :31/:124, `actions/setup-python@v6` at :32,\n`actions/upload-artifact@v7` at :43, `actions/download-artifact@v8` at :60/:85);\ninstalls build tools with unrestricted upgrades (`pip install --upgrade build`\n:37, `--upgrade twine` :41); publishes via the branch-like `pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish@release/v1`\n(:65); declares the build backend as bare `hatchling` (`pyproject.toml:1-3`); and\nin the `mcp_registry` job downloads its publisher from a mutable `releases/latest`\nURL and executes it **without a digest/signature check** (:129) in a job that holds\n`id-token: write` (used for GitHub OIDC login + registry publication). None of the\ncheckouts set `persist-credentials: false`, so the token persists in local git\nconfig by default. The repo already SHA-pins actions in `gerrit-verify.yaml` and\n`_optionality.yml`, so `release.yml` is inconsistent with the repo's own convention.\n\n## What\n\nAdopt the uv / pip pinning pattern (uv: full-SHA action pins, `persist-credentials:\nfalse`, a pinned release tool with a verified SHA-256; pip: SHA-pinned actions +\na hash-locked build environment installed with `--require-hashes --no-deps`):\n\n- Replace each action tag with a full commit SHA, keeping the human-readable\n  version in a trailing comment.\n- Set `persist-credentials: false` on every release checkout unless a later git\n  operation demonstrably needs the persisted credential.\n- Create a reviewed release lock/constraints file covering `build`, Hatchling,\n  Twine, any artifact-validation tools, and their transitive deps; install it with\n  hashes and build without further isolated resolution. **Because pip's default\n  `python -m build` resolves the `[build-system]` requires in a fresh isolated env,\n  the lock only governs Hatchling's version if the build uses the pre-installed\n  locked env** — so either pin Hatchling in `pyproject.toml` `[build-system]`\n  requires *in addition to* the lock, or pass `--no-build-isolation` with the\n  pre-installed locked env, and add a workflow lint/test step that fails if the\n  enforcing mechanism is absent (close the free-resolution remainder vector).\n- **MCP publisher — verify before the OIDC-privileged step.** Replace the\n  `releases/latest` URL with an exact version. First confirm whether\n  `modelcontextprotocol/registry` releases ship per-artifact checksums (a\n  `checksums.txt` / `.sha256`); if they do, download-then-verify; if they do **not**,\n  hard-code the SHA-256 computed at pin time (`echo \"<sha256>  mcp-publisher.tar.gz\"\n  | sha256sum -c`) and document that fallback. **Security contract:** the\n  `id-token: write` (OIDC) scope must not be co-resident with an unverified binary —\n  the digest check must pass *before* `./mcp-publisher login github-oidc` runs (i.e.\n  before the OIDC token is minted/used). Fail on an unexpected filename/size/digest/version.\n- Print and retain in release evidence: every action SHA, the Python build-tool\n  versions, the MCP publisher version + downloaded digest, and the wheel/sdist digests.\n- Update pins through reviewed dependency-update changes, not implicit resolution\n  during a production release.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `.github/workflows/release.yml` — SHA-pin all `uses:`; `persist-credentials:\n  false`; hash-locked build install; exact-version + digest-verified MCP publisher\n  (coordinate with Findings 1 and 3, which also edit this file).\n- A new release build lock/constraints file (e.g. under `.github/` or `requirements/`).\n- `pyproject.toml` — no functional change required to the unpinned `[build-system]`\n  requires (the lock governs the isolated build env), but document the intent.\n- `docs/releasing.md` — document the pinning policy and the pin-update process.\n  **Section ownership:** this story owns the \"Pinning\" section only (Finding 1 owns\n  \"Release-source authorization\", Finding 3 owns \"Build-once\"), avoiding overlap\n  across the three concurrent release stories.\n- Out of scope: pinning non-release workflows already SHA-pinned; full reproducible\n  builds (covered adjacent to Finding 3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Every `uses:` in `release.yml` references a full 40-char commit SHA with a\n  trailing version comment — verified by a workflow-lint/grep check (extendable from\n  the repo's existing SHA-pin convention in `gerrit-verify.yaml`) that fails if any\n  `uses:` in `release.yml` is a tag/branch rather than a 40-hex SHA.\n- [ ] Every release checkout sets `persist-credentials: false`.\n- [ ] Release build tools (`build`, Hatchling, Twine, validation tools) install from\n  a reviewed hash-locked file with `--require-hashes` — verified by the release\n  install step using the lock file and by two builds at the same source SHA\n  resolving byte-identical tool versions (recorded in release evidence).\n- [ ] Hatchling's version is enforced end-to-end: either pinned in `pyproject.toml`\n  `[build-system]` requires or built with `--no-build-isolation` against the\n  pre-installed locked env, with a workflow lint/test step that fails if the\n  enforcing mechanism is removed (no free-resolution path remains).\n- [ ] The MCP publisher is pinned to an exact version and its archive digest is\n  verified before execution, and the digest check passes **before** the OIDC login /\n  token use (the `id-token: write` scope is never co-resident with an unverified\n  binary), failing on a mismatch — verified by a CI check that substituting a different\n  archive for the pinned one causes the step to exit non-zero before\n  `mcp-publisher login`/execution. If upstream ships no checksums, the pinned SHA-256\n  is hard-coded in the workflow with a rationale comment.\n- [ ] Release evidence records all action SHAs, build-tool versions, the MCP\n  publisher version + digest, and the wheel/sdist digests.\n- [ ] `docs/releasing.md` documents the pinning policy and pin-update process.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass, and the change lands via the\n  Gerrit two-vote gate."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784047543778180001,"uuid":"fe449541-b5fd-4b6c-be0b-2fab26449de0"}